Hosting the 2048 game on kubernetes.
The Dockerfile provided in this repo is used to install all the dependencies needed for the game to be hosted on k8s.
The game app is containerized an is easily portable.
To get the game running follow the steps below:
    Build the dockerfile to get an image
    Push the image to Dockerhub
    Create a deployment yaml file and implement it.
    Your k8s cluster is now hosting the game. 
You can verify it by giving the node ip: port number.
